rdf:Description.lla:note: Includes note of 30 March 1871 from David Jones regarding not including the discharge of part of his crew at Hamburg and Cuxhaven in the official logbook. Ship owner: Thomas Roberts, Aberystwith.
Surname could be Gadwin, Gadwer, Gadira, Gadera or Gadwa. St Jhns may refer to the port of St John's, Newfoundland. Cuxhaven is a port in Germany.
Saleshear could be phonetic spelling of Salacia, registered at Newcastle 1860.

Date left ship given as 1870-02-22 but voyage dates would make it 1871, as voyage did not begin until 1870-08-15. No record found for Landore in 1870, a ship with the same name was built at Liverpool 1890.
A ship called the Ashgrove was registered at Port Glasgow 1870.
Surname could also be Henrys or Henngs
Last ship's port could refer to Sydney, Australia or Sidney, British Columbia, Canada. Reserve commission number: 39253.
Name could be J Preiss (long f). Birth place: Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada.
